5:
Heh. I eat junk metal like that for 
breakfast.
13:
Um, hi! Or, uh... "sumimasen"? "Buenos 
dias"? "Ni hao"? Can you understand 
me?
19:
Yes. Your language is comprehensible 
to us.
22:
Ugh, thank goodness. 
'Cause I was worri—
 ...Wait. Wait, wait, wait. Huh? NO WAY!
26:
Carbon lifeforms?! 100% organic?! 
I can't believe it! Humans! Real, live 
humans!
30:
Oh my gooosh... Your cheeks, they're 
so soft. It's like smooshing memory 
foam…
39:
Hey, metal mask! Claws to yourself, 
okay?!
43:
*gasp* A FURBALL. I'm gonna name 
you Fwed and hug you and squeeze 
you!
47:
That's enough, magnet fingers. Tell us 
who you are.
51:
Oh, sure—
Wait, no! YOU'RE the intruders. YOU tell 
me who YOU are.
59:
And I'm Alk. The big furball is Nimbus, 
and the little furball is Light.
68:
Oh. That went... smoother than I was 
expecting.
70:
I'm Dia! Or, I guess if you want to go by 
my production certificate, it's Diva 
Media... but everyone just calls me Dia.
73:
I'm your resident golden canary! I... uh, 
sing. You know…
78:
When Diva Media's on the air, all your 
electrons stop and stare!
87: Oh. I get it. You're a pop star!
92:
Phew. I'm glad you figured it out. 
I was starting to overheat…
99:
Yeah. I'm a droid. An android, to be 
exact.
101:
An android... This civilization is even 
more advanced than I had previously 
supposed.
103:
That pillar of light was you guys, right? 
Did you get beamed down by a UFO or 
something?
104:
We've spent so long searching for 
planets with organic lifeforms, and 
never found so much as a stinking cell.
109: Oh. Yeah, we're from a whole different—
115:
Oh no... I don't think the 
Administrator's very happy.
117:
Come over to my place! You'll get 
caught, wandering around the city.
119:
Besides, I still have a heap of questions 
to ask you.
124: I think we can trust her.
132: It's settled then. Lead the way, Dia.
137:
There's a bunch of bugs up ahead. 
Stay alert!
